<BaseHead />
<Header />

<main class="container">
  <h2>Human Resources</h2>
  <div style="background-color: #fff8c6; border: 1px solid #999; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 14px;">
    ⚠️ Access to restricted departments without clearance is a violation of Section 8-B of the Conduct Agreement. Proceed with authorization only.
  </div>

  <form style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
    <label for="directory-search"><b>Search Employee Directory:</b></label><br />
    <input type="text" id="directory-search" name="directory-search" placeholder="Enter employee name..." size="30" disabled style="margin-top: 5px;">
    <p style="font-size: 10px; color: gray;">* Directory Search is currently offline pending compliance upgrade.</p>
  </form>

  <p>
    The Human Resources Department ensures proper compliance with company conduct guidelines, emotional tone, and behavior modulation. They are responsible for onboarding, disciplinary review, and loyalty alignment.
  </p>
  <p><b>Department Head:</b> Chief Human Resources Officer</p>
  <p><b>Key Initiatives:</b></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Routine morale assessments</li>
    <li>Mandatory seminars: "Optimizing Output Through Enthusiasm"</li>
    <li>Internal grievance compression unit (IGCU)</li>
  </ul>
  <p style="margin-top: 20px; font-size: 12px; color: gray;">
    Last reviewed: 1999.3.4 · Only cleared employees may request offboarding forms.
  </p>

  <hr />
